<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; INFORMATION FAIR FOR PARENTS TO BE HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 30 community organizations will offer parents free information about 
their services during a special fair today at Morningside Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
 Called "CARE Night" -- short for "Community Assistance Resources Education" -- 
the fair will include groups such as the Orange County Health Care Agency, 
Vietnamese Community of Orange County and the Boys' and Girls' Clubs, school 
district spokesman Alan Trudell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials from Morningside and Excelsior elementary schools will play host to 
the fair, which is designed to provide parents with a better understanding of 
programs available to them. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove police will offer free fingerprinting for children 5 and older. 
Translators will be provided for parents who speak Spanish and Vietnamese. 
</P>
<P>
 The event begins at 7 p.m. in the multipurpose room at Morningside Elementary, 
10521 Morningside Drive. JON NALICK 
</P>
