<HEADLINE>
<P>
REP. HUGHES ANNOUNCES PLANS TO LEAVE CONGRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rep. William J. Hughes (D-N.J.) announced his retirement Monday, saying that 
after two decades in Congress it was time to give others a chance at government 
service. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes is the 30th member -- 15 from each party -- to announce retirement from 
the House at the end of this session. 
</P>
<P>
 He did not specify his immediate plans. 
</P>
