<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; PROCHASKA, HARRELL LEAD KENNEDY OVERTIME VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kennedy defeated Santiago, 62-58, in overtime in a Garden Grove League girls' 
basketball game Monday at Santiago High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Leslie Prochaska, who scored 19 points, helped Kennedy to an 11-point lead 
after three quarters, but Santiago outscored the Fighting Irish, 20-9, in the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Rayna Harrell made a three-point basket with three seconds remaining in 
regulation to send the game into overtime. Harrell finished with 12 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In a free-throw filled overtime, Prochaska scored the only field goal as the 
Fighting Irish held on for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Cunningham and Erryn Gutjahr each scored 12 points for Kennedy (13-7, 
6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Cari Remmel had 19 points and 17 rebounds and Jennifer Morris added 12 points 
and 16 rebounds for Santiago (5-13, 2-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Garden Grove League girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 48, Pacifica 37 -- Nicole Murray scored a game-high 24 points for 
Garden Grove (7-10, 5-3). Pilar Surch had 12 for Pacifica (6-11, 2-6). 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 63, Bolsa Grande 12 -- Linda Rodriguez scored 28 and Rhonda 
Gondringer had 13 points and 11 rebounds for La Quinta (14-4, 8-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos 61, Los Amigos 34 -- Akilah Rodgers scored 26 points and 
grabbed 22 rebounds, and Julie Littman had 13 points for Rancho Alamitos (13-6, 
7-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 93, Garden Grove 80 -- Chris Vlasic scored 27 points and Ramon 
Alliman 25 to lead seventh-ranked Pacifica (17-1, 8-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago 61, Kennedy 50 -- Henry Johnson scored 25 points to help Santiago 
(8-12, 3-5) defeat Kennedy (5-14, 3-5) for the first time in the seven seasons 
the Fighting Irish have been in the Garden Grove League. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 53, Rancho Alamitos 51 -- Los Amigos (9-10, 5-3) trailed, 33-19, at 
halftime but held Rancho Alamitos (3-5 in league) to five third-quarter points. 
Chris Yu had 15 points for Los Amigos and Carlos Sianez had 14 points and 10 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 65, Bolsa Grande 47 -- Kevin Doane had 17 points and 14 rebounds and 
Greg Greenfield had 17 points to lead La Quinta (10-9, 4-4). 
</P>
