<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gil Gonzales 
</P>
<P>
 Orange, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales led Orange County with 92 three-point baskets last season. Although 
that pace has slowed, Orange coaches are happier with Gonzales' play because of 
his improved defense, rebounding, passing and shooting percentage. Friday, 
against then-No. 3 Santa Ana Valley, Gonzales had 22 points, including five 
three-pointers, and a season-high 12 rebounds as the Panthers won, 64-58, and 
moved into sole possession of first place in the Century League. Wednesday, 
Gonzales had 15 points and seven rebounds in a 61-56 victory over El Modena. 
</P>
<P>
 Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Greg Abbott, Troy, who averaged 22 points in Freeway League victories over 
Sunny Hills and Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jason Fikse, Esperanza, posted his third and fourth consecutive Empire 
League shutouts, a 0-0 tie with Los Alamitos and 2-0 over Loara. 
</P>
<P>
 * Judd Nester, Capistrano Valley, scored two goals in a 4-0 soccer victory 
over Dana Hills and one in a 3-0 victory over then-No. 1 Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ali Ton, Los Alamitos, had 24 points and 11 assists in a 77-59 victory over 
Katella and seven points and 10 assists in a 69-41 victory over Esperanza. 
</P>
