<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nicole Erickson's free throws to open the second half of Brea-Olinda's 65-49 
victory over Mater Dei on Saturday gave her the school's career-scoring record. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson surpassed Aimee McDaniel, who scored 1,797 points from 1987-90, with 
her 10th point of the night. She finished with 20 points, giving her 1,808 with 
six regular-season games remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 If she maintains her 16-point average, her projected 2,032 points would place 
her 10th on the Southern Section all-time career scoring list. 
</P>
<P>
 After the game, she downplayed the record. "It's nice," she said, "but what 
I'm looking for won't be until March." 
</P>
<P>
 The State finals are March 19. MARTIN HENDERSON 
