<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY-AREA BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; HENRY LEADS VALLEY COLLEGE TO 102-94 WIN OVER 
GLENDALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Valley College freshman Kenneth Henry scored 30 points and grabbed 10 rebounds 
to lead the Monarchs to a 102-94 victory over Glendale in a Western State 
Conference game played Monday at Notre Dame High. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Grayson added 20 points and 15 rebounds and Darius Moses tallied 16 
points and 16 rebounds for Valley (9-12, 3-3 in conference play, 1-0 in 
Southern Division play). WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 81, Glendale 65 -- Monarch guard Vonya Dangerfield had 19 points and 12 
rebounds in a Western State Conference game at Valley (4-3 in conference play, 
1-0 in the Southern Division). Monarch forward Nicole Baines added 17 points, 
nine assists and eight rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 75, Moorpark 59 -- Julie Hardy scored 21 points to lead the Pirates in 
a Western State Conference Northern Division game at Ventura High. Camisca 
Hawkins added 16 points, 11 rebounds and seven steals for Ventura (17-4, 7-0, 
1-0). 
</P>
