<P>
 Texaco's 1st Quarter Earnings Up 8.3%: In the final three months of 1993, 
Texaco's earnings rose to $339 million, or $1.21 per share, on sales of $8.58 
billion.A year earlier, the company earned $313 million, or $1.11 per share, on 
sales of $9.48 billion. Crude oil prices averaged $4 per barrel lower in the 
quarter, helping cut earnings from exploration and production by 54%. But 
earnings from refining and marketing more than doubled from $83 million to $220 
million. Natural gas prices were slightly below year-ago levels. 
</P>
