<P>
 Film: Hit-starved Columbia Pictures says it finally has a winner in the Mike 
Nichols-directed "Wolf," a romantic thriller starring Jack Nicholson and 
Michelle Pfeiffer. The studio maintains that's why it moved the movie's release 
date from March 30 to June 24, the height of the summer season."We were 
convinced at the most recent screening that we've got a big movie that can 
withstand summer competition," said Jeff Blake, president of distribution. 
Nicholson plays a Manhattan book editor who is bitten on the wrist by a wolf 
and tries to resist being transformed into a beast. The new opening date puts 
the picture up against "The Lion King," an animated Walt Disney musical 
feature, opening nationally that day. "We're willing to trade increased 
competition for better play time," Blake said. TERRY PRISTIN 
