<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: DAVOS; THE ELITE MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business and political leaders from around the world gather in the eastern 
Swiss mountain resort for five days beginning Thursday to discuss world issues 
and economic trends. 
</P>
<P>
 Among leaders who accepted invitations to this year's Davos World Economic 
Forum: Prime Ministers Benazir Bhutto of Pakistan and P. V. Narasimha Rao of 
India, Mexican President Carlos Salinas Gortari, Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shimon Peres and Palestine Liberation Organization chief Yasser Arafat. 
</P>
<P>
 In all, the meeting will attract 800 representatives from industry, 200 
political leaders and 200 leaders from the fields of science and the arts. The 
forum's theme: "Redefining the basic assumptions of the world economy."  
</P>
<P>
 In addition to discussion, the annual event has become known as the venue for 
clinching big business deals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
