<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMI VALLEY'S BRADSHAW FACING SUSPENSION FOR UPCOMING GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Basketball coach Dean Bradshaw of Simi Valley High, who was involved in an 
on-court altercation with a player, will probably not be allowed to coach the 
Pioneers if the team plays its scheduled game Wednesday at Royal, Simi Valley 
Athletic Director George Ragsdale said Monday evening. 
</P>
<P>
 If Bradshaw is prohibited from leading the team, junior varsity coach Steve 
Johnson and sophomore coach Christian Aurand would share coaching duties. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Bradshaw) is suspended until we have an outcome, and I don't think we're 
going to get anything resolved by (Wednesday)," Ragsdale said. "I'm not sure if 
we'll have anything settled before the middle of next week. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd hoped to bring this to a head in a timely fashion, but we haven't been 
able to get all the people together because of the earthquake." 
</P>
<P>
 Bradshaw pushed senior guard Sam Rodriguez, a reserve, in anger late in the 
fourth quarter of the Pioneers' 51-44 victory over Westlake during a Marmonte 
League game Jan. 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012594-0092 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 006956 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
