<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAC-10 WILL NOT PENALIZE LESLIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pacific 10 Conference said Monday it would not penalize USC's Lisa Leslie 
for an altercation during a game at Oregon State on Jan. 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Leslie struck Oregon State's Kristina Lelas with a backhand punch that Oregon 
State Coach Aki Hill said knocked out a tooth. 
</P>
<P>
 Hill called for a two-week suspension of Leslie, but the conference said that 
no action would be taken.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's obvious (Leslie) struck (Lelas) . . . but whether it was flagrant or 
deliberate . . . that can't be determined by what's on the tape," Pac-10 
spokesman Jim Muldoon said.  
</P>
<P>
 Another reason for taking no action, he said, was that game official Mary 
Whatford was in position directly in front of the incident and made no call. 
</P>
<P>
 The videotape also shows Lelas holding Leslie's arm shortly before the punch. 
EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
