<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY & TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacific Telesis, Hewlett-Packard in Pact: The two firms said they have agreed 
to develop technology that will let California customers call up movies and 
other programs "on demand" by late this year or early next.Computer maker 
Hewlett-Packard will supply large "video servers," powerful computers that will 
distribute digital video to consumers' homes. Pacific Bell will provide the 
dial tone network over which the service will be offered. If the FCC approves, 
the service will be available initially in San Diego, Orange County, Los 
Angeles and Silicon Valley. 
</P>
