</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AT&T Seeks to Raise Business Rates: The company said it has proposed increases 
averaging 4% on its business long-distance service and 800 lines. It also 
suggested a restructuring of rates for small businesses under which they could 
receive volume discounts on domestic and basic international long-distance 
services. With FCC approval, the higher rates will be effective Friday and the 
new rate structure will begin March 1. 
</P>
