<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pair of local producers say they will stage Stephen Sondheim's "A Little 
Night Music" in March at the Gem Theatre in Garden Grove, possibly as a prelude 
to mounting an eventual season there. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're renting the theater for this first show, and we're raising the money 
ourselves," Beth Hansen said."We're also in negotiations with the Gem for a 
1994-95 season. If all this works out, we would be an independent company in 
residence there." 
</P>
<P>
 Hansen would star as Desiree in the musical. She is a partner with George 
Quick, who would direct, in a small production company called Actors' Cabaret 
Ensemble. "A Little Night Music" would run March 25-April 10. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're looking to raise between $35,000 and $50,000 for the show," Hansen 
said. Phone calls to the Gem went unanswered Monday. The theater has been 
largely inoperative since the collapse of its managing company, 
GroveShakespeare, in June, 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
