<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; SKI-A-THON PLANNED IN BROTHER'S MEMORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was an annual trip they had made since childhood. 
</P>
<P>
 Shellie Woods and her brother, Steve, would head to Mammoth Mountain each 
February for a weekend of skiing in celebration of their birthdays. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was really important that we'd always put that together," Woods said. 
</P>
<P>
 Since her brother's slaying last fall in San Clemente, Woods said, it is more 
important than ever to continue the tradition. 
</P>
<P>
 So she is seeking volunteers and sponsors for ski-a-thon set for Feb. 26 at 
Mammoth Mountain in memory of her 17-year-old brother. Proceeds from the event 
will go to local gang-prevention programs and bring attention to the Oct. 15 
crime that resulted in her brother's death and shocked the community. 
</P>
<P>
 The high school senior was fatally injured when someone plunged a paint roller 
rod through his head as he and a group of friends were trying to drive from a 
confrontation at Calafia County Beach Park. Six people, all alleged members or 
associates of a San Clemente gang, were charged in connection with the slaying. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to send the word about what happened," Woods said. "Instead of it 
being 'Save San Clemente,' let's save California." 
</P>
<P>
 For information on how to help with the event, contact Woods at (714) 
443-9482. ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</TEXT>
