<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; MISSING MAN, 74, IS FOUND SAFE IN TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 74-year-old Camarillo man who had been missing since Friday was found 
sitting in his pickup truck in Santa Clarita and has been returned home, the 
man's wife reported Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Corsetti was reported missing after he left his Camarillo home about 3:30 
p.m. Friday to get gasoline, authorities said.Corsetti is at times forgetful 
and can be disoriented, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorothy Corsetti said she received a call from a Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputy Sunday night, reporting that her husband was healthy and safe at a 
sheriff's station in Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Angeles County authorities became involved when a clerk in a Santa Clarita 
mini-mall spotted Corsetti sitting in his truck in the parking lot for an 
unusual length of time. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think he just got disoriented," Dorothy Corsetti said. "He never had any 
connections in Santa Clarita. He must have gotten on the 126 and kept driving." 
A Ventura County sheriff's deputy confirmed his safe return. "He's home and 
happy and healthy," said Senior Deputy Joe Evans. "He's a delightful man." 
TRACY WILSON 
</P>
