<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: QUAKE VICTIMS CAN ASK FOR REASSESSMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County property owners whose homes or businesses received more than 
$5,000 in damage in the Jan. 17 earthquake should contact the county tax 
assessor's office to have their property reassessed. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications for reassessment must be submitted no later than six months after 
the property was damaged. Here are the numbers for the county assessor's 
office: 
</P>
<P>
 * From Ventura, Ojai or Saticoy: 654-5000 
</P>
<P>
 * From Oxnard, Camarillo or Port Hueneme: 385-8600 
</P>
<P>
 * From Santa Paula: 933-8484 
</P>
<P>
 * From Simi Valley, Thousand Oaks, Moorpark, Newbury Park or Westlake: 
529-2060 
</P>
<P>
 * From Fillmore or Piru: 524-4922 
</P>
<P>
