<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES ; * ROBERT R. NYE; ROAD BUILDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert R. Nye of Ventura, a longtime Ventura County road builder, died 
Saturday at Community Memorial Hospital in Ventura. He was 75. 
</P>
<P>
 Nye, who founded the Robert R. Nye Inc. road construction company in Ventura, 
received one of the state's top construction awards in 1988 for his work on the 
Ojai Valley Trail. He was honored for transforming an abandoned railroad track 
into a landscaped and well-used bicycle and equestrian trail. 
</P>
<P>
 Born in Carrizozo, N. M., Nye moved to Ventura County in 1923 with his 
parents. He attended Ojai schools and obtained a bachelor of science degree in 
civil engineering in 1943 at UC Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
 After college, he joined the Naval Construction Battalion and built airstrips 
in the South Pacific during World War II. 
</P>
<P>
 After the war, he worked for several engineering companies in Los Angeles, 
then founded his own company in 1955. In 1988, he helped his son, Ruric Nye, 
establish another road construction company, Nye & Nelson Inc. of Ventura, in 
1988. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Nye was a charter member and past president of the tri-counties chapter 
of Associated General Contractors of America and was a state board member. 
Active in the Rotary Club, he was a Rotary Paul Harris fellow, the highest 
Rotarian award. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to his son, survivors include his wife, Pilar; daughter Pamela, of 
Marin County; sister Mary Nye Pierpont of Ojai, and two grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 Services will be at 2 p.m. Wednesday at the Ted Mayr Funeral Home in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Avendano, David L., 35, of Ojai, repair technician for Southern California 
Edison. Pierce Brothers Stetler Mortuary, Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, Mary W., 95, of Thousand Oaks, retired college professor. Pierce 
Brothers Valley Oaks, Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 Rutia, Remedios R., 86, of Ventura, homemaker. Joseph P. Reardon Funeral 
Chapel, Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, Kenneth E., 82, of Ventura, dentist. Ted Mayr Funeral Home, Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County obituaries are published free of charge as a public service to 
readers. Obituaries are based on information provided by mortuaries. 
</P>
