<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: NEW IMAGE REPORTS FLAT EARNINGS, HIGHER REVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Image Industries Inc., a Canoga Park company that sells intraoral cameras 
and dental imaging equipment, reported that its fiscal second-quarter earnings 
were essentially flat at $1.42 million, compared to $1.44 million in net income 
a year before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's revenue for the three months ended Dec. 31 rose 36%, to $10.9 
million from $8.03 million.It said the results reflected growing demand from 
dentists for its products. 
</P>
<P>
 It also said that its fiscal second-quarter profit would have increased 71% 
from a year earlier without the results of Styles on Video, its former 
subsidiary that was spun off to shareholders last March. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, New Image earned $2.1 million, down 6% from $2.23 million 
a year earlier. Its revenue rose 21%, to $16.4 million from $13.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
