<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ARCS MORTGAGE REPORTS 6% RISE IN EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ARCS Mortgage Inc., the Calabasas-based mortgage banking affiliate of Bank of 
New York, said its mortgage originations in the year ended Dec. 20 rose 20% 
over the previous year, and its profit increased 6%. 
</P>
<P>
 ARCS said it originated $3.69 billion in new mortgage loans in the latest 
year. Refinancings were a major contributor to the growth, it said, although 
new loan activity is also increasing. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said the share of delinquent loan payments fell slightly in 1993 
to 3.21% from 3.27% in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
