</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 22; Column 2; National Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
52 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONVICTED DRUG USER IS LITERALLY FLUSHED OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Negotiations and tear gas were not enough to persuade a convicted drug user to 
surrender, so police decided to flush him out with 2,500 gallons of water. 
</P>
<P>
 A cold and wet Charles Stiles, 39, emerged from his house into 30-degree 
temperatures Sunday and was treated for hypothermia. Then police took him to 
jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
